{"article_id":"VqFoHE2uUvn2clRC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights Obama :","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"U.S. has no military strategy yet","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"on what to do against ISIS in Syria","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"There 's been no hint of ground forces ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"but commandos did do a rescue mission","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"Airstrikes are a possibility ;","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"a congressman says","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"it 's critical U.S. work with locals","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"`` There is no such thing as a no-risk strategy , ''","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"Rep. Adam Smith adds","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"If the United States is serious about thoroughly defeating ISIS ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"it must","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"-- somehow , some way --","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"go through Syria .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Those are the big questions now ,","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"as President Barack Obama weighs what to do inside the war-ravaged nation","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"where ISIS leaders are based","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"and where the Islamist terror group rose to prominence .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"Obama ceded Thursday","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"that `` we do n't have a strategy yet ''","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"for what to do about ISIS inside Syria ,","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"with a senior administration official adding","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that a decision is `` a week or so '' away .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"Critics hammer Obama over ISIS threat","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"Critics hammer Obama over ISIS threat","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"01:49","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"Analysis :","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"Obama 's strategy for ISIS","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"MUST WATCH Analysis :","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Obama 's strategy for ISIS 07:51","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"What led another American to ISIS ?","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"What led another American to ISIS ?","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"01:55","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"`` There is no such thing as a no-risk strategy , ''","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"said Rep. Adam Smith , D-Washington .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"`` It 's a matter of taking the right risk","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"and balancing that risk","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"to make the right choice . ''","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Here 's a look at some possibilities ,","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"including why and how they could and could not work :","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"When terrorists attacked on September 11 , 2001 ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"the United States showed its willingness","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"to use its full military might","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"when it attacked Afghanistan","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"-- a campaign","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"that dragged on for years","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"and killed more than 2,300 American troops .","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"That steep cost , both human and financial , is the big reason","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"this is very , very unlikely to happen again in Syria .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"No U.S. officials have suggested troops on the ground .","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"The fact","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"none were sent to fight in Iraq","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"-- a country","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"where the U.S. has deeper ties and a government","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"it works with --","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"is further indication","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"there will be no U.S. ground invasion of Syria anytime soon .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"There could be smaller-scale , targeted operations , though .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"After all , Pentagon spokesman Rear Adm. John Kirby told CNN","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"that , this summer , elite U.S. commandos from units like Delta Force and Navy SEAL Team 6 went into Syria","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"and tried to rescue American journalist James Foley and others","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"held by Islamic militants .","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"They did n't find hostages ,","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"but who 's to say U.S. Special Operations Forces could n't conduct more such missions","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"to save others or for some other purpose ?","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"Then there 's the possibility","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"American troops could go into Syria","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"to help with the targeting of U.S. airstrikes .","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"Of course , all bets are off","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"if ISIS pulls an al Qaeda","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"and strikes inside the United States .","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"That has n't happened yet ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"though some experts believe","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"that such an attack from ISIS","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"-- which ,","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"upon beheading Foley ,","depth":16},{"id":84,"text":"warned","depth":17},{"id":85,"text":"other U.S. citizens could be next --","depth":17},{"id":86,"text":"might be a matter of time .","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"Obama gave the go-ahead","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"to pound ISIS forces in Iraq from the air .","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"Why not do the same in Syria ,","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"a country","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"the President himself ceded Thursday","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"has become a `` safe haven '' for the terror group ?","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"It starts with the fact that Syria is a mess .","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"Three years of civil war have torn apart the country ,","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"spurring the emergence of rebel groups","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"fighting to oust President Bashar al-Assad","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"and sometimes against each other .","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"About the only thing","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"al-Assad and rebel groups have in common","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"is that ISIS is their enemy .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"Obama is pushing to get al-Assad too ,","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"but they 're on the same side","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"when it comes to ISIS .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"Yet U.S. officials insist","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"this shared cause does n't mean","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"they 'll coordinate any military action with al-Assad 's government ,","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"even if Syrian officials are demanding it .","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"It 's one thing to anger Syria even more .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"It 's another thing to anger its allies Iran and Russia .","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"Russia ,","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"which is already at odds with the West over Ukraine ,","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"could block any U.N. Security Council effort","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"to give a seal of approval to international strikes .","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"All of this brings many questions :","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"Does the United States really want to conduct a military campaign in a country","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"without a government","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"that is stable","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"and that it trusts ?","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"Can it count on opposition factions","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"it supports","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"to provide any long-term stability ?","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"And does it know","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"that airstrikes will wipe out ISIS in Syria","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"rather than stalling the group ?","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"Absent a fortune-teller ,","depth":5},{"id":126,"text":"it 's hard to tell how any military action would turn out .","depth":5},{"id":127,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":6},{"id":128,"text":"Lawmaker :","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"ISIS strategy has to be smart","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"Lawmaker :","depth":6},{"id":133,"text":"ISIS strategy has to be smart","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"04:36","depth":5},{"id":135,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":6},{"id":136,"text":"Does Obama have a strategy for ISIS ?","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"Does Obama have a strategy for ISIS ?","depth":6},{"id":140,"text":"02:23","depth":6},{"id":141,"text":"Still ,","depth":6},{"id":142,"text":"if Obama decides that 's the way to go now ,","depth":8},{"id":143,"text":"White House spokesman Josh Earnest stressed ,","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"more needs to be done politically , diplomatically and economically long-term","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"to keep ISIS down .","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"`` Any sort of strategy","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"that 's predicated only on the use of American military force","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"will not be an enduring solution , ''","depth":7},{"id":149,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":150,"text":"The Obama administration frequently touts its support for `` moderate opposition ''","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"battling both al-Assad 's forces and ISIS .","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"Yet , for all its talk , it has n't directly armed such forces .","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"The ideal is ,","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"if you arm groups like the Free Syrian Army ,","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"they can help take out ISIS .","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"That may not be realistic ,","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"considering ISIS with the Syrian government may be the most powerful forces now in the nation .","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"Then there 's the real possibility","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"that","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"if moderate forces lose ,","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"American weaponry may end up in the hands of ISIS ,","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"as has happened in Iraq .","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"Still , it helps to have someone local","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"you trust","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"to provide on-the-ground intelligence for airstrikes","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"or compliment those strikes with a ground assault .","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"Smith , the Democrats ' ranking member on the House Armed Services Committee , is among those","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"who believes","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"`` U.S. military might alone is not going to contain ISIS .","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"We are going to need partners locally . ''","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"`` We have to strengthen them ,","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"not so much","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"so they can win , ''","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"Smith said of the Free Syria movement ,","depth":11},{"id":175,"text":"`` but so that they can survive","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"and maintain some territory","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"to give us a partner","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"to work with . ''","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"If you ca n't pound ISIS into submission militarily ,","depth":8},{"id":180,"text":"the reasoning goes ,","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"you can hit it where it hurts :","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"the wallet .","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"The thinking goes that ,","depth":9},{"id":184,"text":"in order to wage war ,","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"you need weapons , vehicles , ammunition .","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"In order to govern a country ,","depth":9},{"id":187,"text":"you need access to food , water and electricity .","depth":9},{"id":188,"text":"And usually","depth":7},{"id":189,"text":"to address these needs ,","depth":8},{"id":190,"text":"a group needs money .","depth":8},{"id":191,"text":"Implementing sanctions and freezing bank accounts are often the first , least controversial steps","depth":7},{"id":192,"text":"to go after a terrorist group .","depth":7},{"id":193,"text":"And they can have an impact ,","depth":8},{"id":194,"text":"but they also have their limits .","depth":8},{"id":195,"text":"For one , one should n't think","depth":10},{"id":196,"text":"such efforts will be effective overnight .","depth":10},{"id":197,"text":"They take time","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"to coordinate ,","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"and it takes time","depth":11},{"id":200,"text":"to drain militants ' piggy banks .","depth":11},{"id":201,"text":"Plus , it 's not like there 's a readily available list of ISIS donors","depth":9},{"id":202,"text":"to go after .","depth":9},{"id":203,"text":"And the fact is ,","depth":8},{"id":204,"text":"ISIS is n't like many other terror groups .","depth":8},{"id":205,"text":"Unlike others like al Qaeda , it 's chief goal is as practical","depth":9},{"id":206,"text":"as it is ideological :","depth":9},{"id":207,"text":"to take over","depth":9},{"id":208,"text":"and govern territory .","depth":9},{"id":209,"text":"Already , ISIS has proven adept at seizing weaponry .","depth":7},{"id":210,"text":"It 's also paid attention to things like food stocks , electricity , sewage , medical care and more ,","depth":8},{"id":211,"text":"as a recent Foreign Policy article noted .","depth":8},{"id":212,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":213,"text":"ISIS vs. Al Qaeda :","depth":10},{"id":214,"text":"How they 're different","depth":10},{"id":215,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":216,"text":"MUST WATCH ISIS vs. Al Qaeda :","depth":9},{"id":217,"text":"How they 're different","depth":9},{"id":218,"text":"02:03","depth":8},{"id":219,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":220,"text":"ISIS recruiting fighters from Minnesota ?","depth":11},{"id":221,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":222,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":11},{"id":223,"text":"ISIS recruiting fighters from Minnesota ?","depth":11},{"id":224,"text":"02:09","depth":10},{"id":225,"text":"JUST WATCHED Obama :","depth":12},{"id":226,"text":"Need regional anti-ISIS coalition","depth":12},{"id":227,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":228,"text":"MUST WATCH Obama :","depth":11},{"id":229,"text":"Need regional anti-ISIS coalition","depth":11},{"id":230,"text":"01:49","depth":9},{"id":231,"text":"`` They are in this for the long haul , ''","depth":9},{"id":232,"text":"Rep. Mike Rogers , R-Michigan , said .","depth":9},{"id":233,"text":"`` They are trying to structure themselves in a way","depth":9},{"id":234,"text":"that they can hold","depth":10},{"id":235,"text":"and expand their holdings . ''","depth":10},{"id":236,"text":"Whether its government is effective or not ,","depth":8},{"id":237,"text":"one thing","depth":9},{"id":238,"text":"ISIS has proven","depth":9},{"id":239,"text":"is its zealousness for the cause and willingness","depth":8},{"id":240,"text":"to sacrifice civilians","depth":9},{"id":241,"text":"who have n't believed in it from the beginning .","depth":9},{"id":242,"text":"One big thing","depth":10},{"id":243,"text":"the United States has going for it :","depth":10},{"id":244,"text":"Practically no one likes ISIS .","depth":9},{"id":245,"text":"Sure , there are groups and individuals","depth":10},{"id":246,"text":"backing the formation of an Islamic State","depth":11},{"id":247,"text":"-- which is what ISIS calls itself","depth":13},{"id":248,"text":"now that it controls a vast swath of Syria and Iraq --","depth":13},{"id":249,"text":"governed by sharia law .","depth":12},{"id":250,"text":"Some from oil-rich Muslim states in the Middle East may bankroll the group ;","depth":10},{"id":251,"text":"others fight ,","depth":11},{"id":252,"text":"with U.S. Attorney General Eric Holder this summer estimating","depth":12},{"id":253,"text":"that there are 7,000 such foreigners with militant groups in Syria .","depth":12},{"id":254,"text":"`` There are clearly two camps in the world today :","depth":9},{"id":255,"text":"those","depth":11},{"id":256,"text":"who believe","depth":13},{"id":257,"text":"that sovereignty and supremacy in the world belongs to God ,","depth":13},{"id":258,"text":"they are the Islamic State ,","depth":12},{"id":259,"text":"( and ) those","depth":11},{"id":260,"text":"who believe","depth":12},{"id":261,"text":"sovereignty belongs to man , ''","depth":12},{"id":262,"text":"said British firebrand preacher Anjem Choudhary ,","depth":9},{"id":263,"text":"who sides with the Islamic State .","depth":9},{"id":264,"text":"Yet ISIS has far , far more detractors than supporters .","depth":8},{"id":265,"text":"It has a bloody track record of beheadings , crucifixions , stonings , not to mention the widespread slaughtering of minorities , Christians and Muslims","depth":10},{"id":266,"text":"who do n't prescribe to its strict interpretation of Islam .","depth":10},{"id":267,"text":"Such actions","depth":11},{"id":268,"text":"-- like Foley 's execution --","depth":11},{"id":269,"text":"spurred widespread condemnation .","depth":10},{"id":270,"text":"Some have incentive to go beyond condemnation","depth":9},{"id":271,"text":"and act , militarily , against ISIS .","depth":9},{"id":272,"text":"Start with nations","depth":12},{"id":273,"text":"that border Syria ,","depth":12},{"id":274,"text":"like Jordan and Turkey .","depth":11},{"id":275,"text":"As its self-ordained caliphate shows ,","depth":13},{"id":276,"text":"ISIS has shown","depth":14},{"id":277,"text":"that it does n't abide by national borders .","depth":14},{"id":278,"text":"What 's to stop it from advancing into another country ,","depth":13},{"id":279,"text":"especially if it gets bigger , stronger and richer ?","depth":13},{"id":280,"text":"That possibility might spur other countries , besides the United States , to step in sooner rather than later .","depth":11},{"id":281,"text":"Even if they do n't neighbor Iraq or Syria ,","depth":12},{"id":282,"text":"nations with significant populations of Sunnis","depth":14},{"id":283,"text":"-- which is the sect of most Muslims worldwide , including in Middle Eastern nations like Saudi Arabia and Egypt --","depth":14},{"id":284,"text":"may have reason","depth":14},{"id":285,"text":"to worry .","depth":14},{"id":286,"text":"Like with al Qaeda previously , disaffected young Muslims anywhere","depth":14},{"id":287,"text":"-- even in the West --","depth":14},{"id":288,"text":"could join ISIS ,","depth":13},{"id":289,"text":"then perhaps deciding to act out in their homelands .","depth":12},{"id":290,"text":"`` It 's certainly not in the interest of governments in that neighborhood to have ( ISIS ) wreaking havoc","depth":12},{"id":291,"text":"or perpetrating terrible acts of violence , ''","depth":12},{"id":292,"text":"said Earnest , the White House spokesman .","depth":11},{"id":293,"text":"These nations could band together .","depth":8},{"id":294,"text":"The United States could be part of this coalition ,","depth":9},{"id":295,"text":"perhaps letting others take an equal or greater role in military operations .","depth":9},{"id":296,"text":"The idea","depth":10},{"id":297,"text":"of Washington leading `` from behind ''","depth":10},{"id":298,"text":"has precedent :","depth":9},{"id":299,"text":"look at Libya .","depth":9},{"id":300,"text":"This international coalition got what it wanted with the downfall of dictator Moammar Gadhafi .","depth":10},{"id":301,"text":"But years later , Libya is not a model of anything good :","depth":11},{"id":302,"text":"beset by warring militias and without an effective central government .","depth":11},{"id":303,"text":"Rogers , the House Intelligence committee chairman , thinks","depth":7},{"id":304,"text":"the Obama administration has had `` no real strategy '' on ISIS so far","depth":9},{"id":305,"text":"-- especially a strategy","depth":10},{"id":306,"text":"that addresses the group 's base in Syria --","depth":10},{"id":307,"text":"even though the group 's been growing stronger for years .","depth":8},{"id":308,"text":"`` We 're so far along into this , ''","depth":8},{"id":309,"text":"the Republican said of ISIS 's rise .","depth":8},{"id":310,"text":"`` It 's not like this happened just last week . ''","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":621,"left":437,"right":620,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":437,"left":333,"right":436,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":333,"left":0,"right":332,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":332,"left":323,"right":331,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":323,"left":317,"right":322,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":317,"left":312,"right":316,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":312,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":316,"left":313,"right":315,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":313,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":315,"left":5,"right":314,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":314,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":322,"left":318,"right":321,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":318,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":321,"left":10,"right":320,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":320,"left":319,"right":13,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":319,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":331,"left":326,"right":330,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":3